        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 4:15PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM CDT, strong thunderstorms were clustered along a line
extending from 8 miles southwest of Glenfield to 5 miles southwest
of Kensal to 6 miles southwest of Bordulac. Movement was east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Kensal, Glenfield, Bordulac, Pingree, Courtenay, Melville, Edmunds,
and Juanita.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
